## Interview Quick Revision

| Function | Purpose       |
| -------- | ------------- |
| COUNT()  | Count rows    |
| SUM()    | Total value   |
| AVG()    | Average value |
| MIN()    | Lowest value  |
| MAX()    | Highest value |

### Expected TCS/Java Developer Question

**Q:** Difference between COUNT(*) and COUNT(column)?

**A:**

* `COUNT(*)` counts all rows.
* `COUNT(column)` counts only non-null values.

Next, learn **GROUP BY and HAVING** because aggregate functions are usually used together with GROUP BY in interviews.
